// PKL-103: `read?(uri)` mirrors `read(uri)` but returns `null`
// instead of pushing a diagnostic when the URI scheme is rejected by
// the sandbox or the resource is missing. The fixture exercises both
// rejection paths: an unknown env var, and a non-`env:` scheme that
// the sandbox doesn't allow.
maybe_missing = read?("env:NONEXISTENT_XYZ_VAR")

maybe_bad_scheme = read?("https://example.com/foo")
